text: Notch expresses interest in a suggestion regarding corals by user "solarblade".

Notch mentioned on his blog: "I tried adding corals, but it's really hard to draw a single block that looks like corals, since it's really more about crazy amounts of variation and diversity. But I do know that the corals will have tiny fish particles around them."
Coral were jokingly teased in the fake snapshot 12marc40awesome, along with fish as mobs and "fish blocks".
Coral fans currently do not generate naturally.
Blue, pink, purple, red, and yellow coral fans have been renamed to tube, brain, bubble, fire, and horn coral fans, respectively.
The textures of all coral fans, except fire coral fans, have been changed.
Coral fans now generate naturally in coral reefs.
5 new sound events that apply to coral fans have been added: block.wet_grass.break, block.wet_grass.fall, block.wet_grass.hit, block.wet_grass.place, and block.wet_grass.step.
Coral fans can now be placed on the tops of blocks.
Coral fans and their dead variants now drop themselves when mined with Silk Touch.
Bone meal used in the water of warm ocean biomes now has a chance of growing coral fans, making them renewable.
Coral fans can be placed on the ground.
The textures of coral fans have been changed.
The textures of dead coral fans have been changed.
The top textures of coral fans have been changed.
Coral fans and their dead variants now drop themselves when mined with Silk Touch.
Bone meal used in water now has a chance of growing coral fans.
